-- Eli Lilly resolves investigations related to Zyprexa
-- 
-- Thu Jan 15, 2009 6:28am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2009/01/15/us-elililly-settlement-idUSTRE50E1OX20090115

 

 (Reuters) - Eli Lilly and Co on Thursday said it resolved investigations of past Zyprexa marketing and promotional practices. 

 Highlights: * Says accepts one misdemeanor charge related to zyprexa promotion between 1999 and 2001 * Says as part of agreement regarding criminal investigation, Lilly has agreed to pay $615 million * Says has agreed to make payments totaling nearly $800 million * Says 2008 charge will be sufficient to cover the payments announced today * Says terms for resolution of civil investigations, lilly has agreed to make payments totaling nearly $800 million * Says agreement will require co to maintain compliance program * Says entered into corporate integrity agreement with office of inspector general of U.S. department of health, human services * Says agreement requires it to maintain compliance program and to undertake set of defined corporate integrity obligations for 5 years